author: jeremiahcp
body: It's like a sine wave, but the coefficient (the amplitude) that controls the stretch or compression is unpredictable.  Bitcoin tends to follow a repeating cycle of ups and downs, like a sine wave. The general pattern is consistent, but the amplitude‚Äîhow high it goes or how low it drops‚Äîvaries each time due to unpredictable factors like market sentiment, regulations, and macro events. So the shape is familiar, but the scale is never the same.  Since Dogecoin nips at the heels of BTC, it follows the same cycle‚Äîbut with even more volatility and unpredictability
